<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08048g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08048g">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08048g"> 48(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> l&apos;agit&eacute; &eacute;crit lent</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">L&apos;artifice choisi est habituellement l&apos;oppos&eacute; de la v&eacute;rit&eacute;. C&apos;est ainsi que les lettres anonymes font la contre-partie de l&apos;&eacute;criture naturelle de l&apos;exp&eacute;diteur. Le grossier &eacute;crit fin; le brouillon espace ses lignes; <mark>l&apos;agit&eacute; trace lentement ses lettres</mark>, l&apos;une apr&egrave;s l&apos;autre; le minutieux s&egrave;me des n&eacute;gligences, etc. <br><font color="green">[The chosen artifice is usually the opposite of the truth. That is why anonymous letters are the counterpart of the natural writing of the forger. Coarse people write very finely; the chaotic space their lines; the agitated trace their letters slowly, one after the other; the careful add mistakes, etc.]</font> <small> J Cr&eacute;pieux-Jamin, <a name="JCJL" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#JCJL"><cite title="source">Les &eacute;l&eacute;ments de l'&eacute;criture des canailles</cite></a> (1923) 275</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
